Section 1:
1 L.D. 767
2 Date: (Filing No. S- )
3 HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 325, L.D. 767, “An Act to Amend the
10 Laws Governing Licensing of Certain Types of Establishments and Professions by the
11 Department of Health and Human Services”
12 Amend the bill in section 3 in §2504 in subsection 2 in paragraph B in the last line
13 (page 2, line 7 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "disclose" and inserting the following:
14 'determine the need for disclosure'
15 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
16 number to read consecutively.
17 SUMMARY
1188 This amendment clarifies that the Commissioner of Health and Human Services may
1199 not delegate the decision to disclose the identity of a complainant or the investigative record
2200 when disclosure is necessary to avoid imminent or serious harm.
2211 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
2222 (See attached)
Page 1 - 132LR0254(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
